## 1. State Update Batching Mechanics
In React functional components, state updates do not immediately trigger a component re-render. Instead, React employs **State Batching** to group multiple state setter triggers into a single re-render cycle, preventing visual layout thrashing and improving frame rates.

### Batching Example
```jsx
function Counter() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  const handleClicks = () => {
    setCount(c => c + 1);
    setCount(c => c + 1);
    setCount(c => c + 1);
    // React groups all 3 updates. The component re-renders exactly once
  };

  return <button onClick={handleClicks}>Clicks: {count}</button>;
}
```
*Note: Prior to React 18, batching was limited to React event handlers. In modern React (v18/19), automatic batching occurs inside promises, timeouts, and native event handlers as well.*

